---
title: Warming Chicken Tinga with Herbed Rice and Zesty Soured Cream
description: If you’ve never made chicken tinga (pronounced teen-GA) before, you’re in for a real treat tonight. Originating from Puebla, Mexico, chicken tinga is a versatile dish of tender chicken in a tomato and chipotle sauce which is traditionally served with tacos or tostadas. Because it’s good to be a little bit different, Chef Lizzie decided to serve it with coriander rice, a limey salad and zesty sour cream.
